{
  format: 1
  name: struct-key-of-eligible-fields-is-valid
  suite: static
  spec: ["§A.8", "§5.4"]
  tags: ["key", "struct"]
  note: '''Annex A.8 (SPEC.md line 4472) lists the types a collection key field MAY use and
names, alongside the scalars, "structs composed solely of key-eligible required fields".
This is the positive of the sibling exclusion cases: `json-type-in-struct-key-excluded`
rejects a struct key with a `json` member, and `optional-key-field-invalid` rejects an
optional key — but A.8 equally MANDATES that a struct whose members are ALL key-eligible
and required is itself a valid `$key`. Here `loc` is a struct of two required
key-eligible fields (`int` + `text`), so the collection MUST load. (A struct key with an
ineligible or optional member would be the excluded case; that laundering path is already
covered adversarially. This case pins the accept side A.8 grants.)'''

  package: {
    $liasse: 1
    $app: "t.structkey.ok@1.0.0"
    $model: {
      cells: {
        $key: "loc"
        loc: {
          x: "int"
          y: "text"
        }
        value: "text"
      }
    }
  }

  expect: {
    outcome: ok
  }
}
